    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are Starrett hole saws compatible with other brands' arbors?",
            "answer": "<p>Starrett hole saws use a standard arbor fitting system. Most Starrett hole saws from 14mm to 210mm fit their A1 and A2 arbor range, which includes a quick-release mechanism for fast blade changes. While some third-party arbors may physically fit, we recommend using <strong>genuine Starrett arbors</strong> for optimal performance and concentricity.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between bi-metal and carbide tipped hole saws?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Bi-metal hole saws</strong> use high-speed steel teeth welded to a spring steel body \u2014 ideal for cutting mild steel, stainless steel, copper, aluminium and wood. <strong>Carbide tipped hole saws</strong> use tungsten carbide teeth for cutting abrasive and difficult materials like nail-embedded wood, fibreglass, reinforced concrete and cast iron. Carbide tipped saws last significantly longer on abrasive materials but cost more upfront.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How should I calibrate Starrett measuring tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Starrett precision measuring tools such as micrometers and calipers are factory-calibrated to exacting standards. For ongoing accuracy, <strong>zero-check your tools</strong> before each use with gauge blocks or reference standards. For formal calibration to traceable standards, contact an accredited calibration laboratory. Starrett also offers calibration services through their authorised network.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Starrett?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Starrett range including hole saws, measuring tools and saw blades. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which Starrett hole saw do I need for plumbing work?",
            "answer": "<p>For plumbing and HVAC work, the <strong>Starrett Fast Cut bi-metal range</strong> is the most popular choice. It cuts cleanly through copper, mild steel and plastic pipe. For cutting through walls where you may hit nails or mixed materials, step up to the <strong>carbide tipped multi-purpose range</strong>. Starrett also offer plumber-specific hole saw kits with the most common diameters.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Where are Starrett tools manufactured?",
            "answer": "<p>Starrett tools are manufactured across <strong>eight facilities worldwide</strong>, including five in the United States (headquartered in Athol, Massachusetts), one in Scotland (serving European and Asian markets since 1958), and facilities in Brazil and China. The Scottish facility means UK customers benefit from locally manufactured products with shorter lead times.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
